# Retail Sales Dashboard (Task 4)

## ðŸ“Œ Objective
Build an interactive Power BI dashboard that helps business stakeholders analyze retail sales, customer behavior, product categories, and payment insights.

## ðŸ“Š Key Dashboard Features
- KPI Cards: Total Revenue, Total Quantity, Total Transactions, Unique Customers, AOV  
- Year-wise Revenue Trend  
- Sales by Category  
- Sales by City (Map)  
- Revenue by Payment Method  
- Filters: Category, Gender, City  
- Clean and consistent color theme  

## ðŸ§® DAX Measures Used
Total Revenue = SUM('synthetic_online_retail_data (1)'[LineTotal])
Total Quantity Sold = SUM('synthetic_online_retail_data (1)'[quantity])
Total Transactions = COUNTROWS('synthetic_online_retail_data (1)')
Unique Customers = DISTINCTCOUNT('synthetic_online_retail_data (1)'[customer_id])
Average Age = AVERAGE('synthetic_online_retail_data (1)'[age])
AOV = DIVIDE([Total Revenue], [Total Transactions], 0)
